<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">The Happiness of Deep Conversations</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Mar 23, 2010 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
The New York Times  <a href="http://well.blogs.nytimes.com/2010/03/17/talk-deeply-be-happy/?src=me&amp;ref=general">recently reported</a> on a study published in  <a href="http://pss.sagepub.com/content/early/2010/02/17/0956797610362675.full"> <i>Psychological Science</i></a> suggesting that people who engage in substantive, meaningful conversations are happier than those who do not.
</p>

 <p>
It appears that Mill was right â€” it is better to be a dissatisfied Socrates than a satisfied pig.
